Name: Back Bay
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled near the area seeded for wild rice.

Name: Back Bay Deep
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled in the deepest part of the bay.

Name: Back Bay Waiskey River
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled at the inlet of a 5th order stream that drains agricultural lands.

Name: Ballpark 1
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: This beach is near the Bay Mills Ball field, is part of an RV Park, and site of festivals and pow wow.  Site 1 is sampled at the west end of the swimming area.

Name: Ballpark 2
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: This beach is near the Bay Mills Ball field, is part of an RV Park, and site of festivals and pow wow.  Site 2 is sampled in the middle of the swimming area.

Name: Ballpark 3
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: This beach is near the Bay Mills Ball field, is part of an RV Park, and site of festivals and pow wow.  Site 3 is sampled at the east end of the swimming area.

Name: Community College Pond
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: The Community College Pond is surrounded by steep sides on the north, west, and south sides.  The east side is a swamp that leads to the beach of the St. Mary's River.

Name: Club Creek Above
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Club Creek Above is a 2nd order stream and is sampled above the Wild Bluff Golf Course.

Name: Club Creek Below
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Club Creek Below is a 2nd order stream and is sampled below the Wild Bluff Golf Course.

Name: Deep Creek
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Deep Creek is a first order stream and is a stained creek that originates in the Wetland Preserve.  There are no houses near this creek.

Name: Gumshoe 1
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Gumshoe is an RV park located on the Upper St. Marys River.  Site 1 is sampled at the west end of the swimming area.

Name: Gumshoe 2
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Gumshoe is an RV park located on the Upper St. Marys River.  Site 2 is sampled in the middle of the swimming area.

Name: Gumshoe 3
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Gumshoe is an RV park located on the Upper St. Marys River.  Site 3 is sampled at the east end of the swimming area.

Name: Long Marsh
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Long Marsh is not part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve.  The wetland is an important cranberry and blueberry collection area.

Name: Little Waishkey Above
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: The Little Waishkey Above is a 2nd order stream that is sampled above an NPDES permited sewage lagoon output.

Name: Little Waishkey Below
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: The Little Waishkey Below is a 2nd order stream that is sampled below an NPDES permited sewage lagoon output.

Name: Monocle Lake
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Monocle Lake is hydrologically connected to Spectacle Lake an important rice lake for the community.  Monocle Lake is also an important sport fishery for bass, perch, and walleye.

Name: North Pond
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: North Pond is a fen that has no houses on the shoreline, but a few houses near the pond.  The east end of the pond has a buffer of trees then Gumshoes RV Park and Campground.

Name: Parish Creek 1
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Parish Creek 1 is a 2nd order stream and is sampled near the parking lot of the Bay Mills Casino and Resort.

Name: Parish Creek 2
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Parish Creek 2 is a 2nd order stream and is sampled near a parking lot drainage system.

Name: Parish Creek Above
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Parish Creek Above is a 2nd order stream and is sampled above the Wild Bluff Golf Course.

Name: Parish Creek Below
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Parish Creek Below is a 2nd order stream and is sampled below the Wild Bluff Golf Course.

Name: Pontys Creek
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Pontys Creek is a first order stream and is sampled below the golf course and where there is sediment deposition from upstream erosion.

Name: Pontys Creek
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Pontys Creek is a first order stream and is sampled below the golf course and where there is sediment deposition from upstream erosion.

Name: Saint Mary's River Shore
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: St. Mary's River is sampled at the shoreline of a populated area with septic tanks.

Name: Spectacle Lake
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Spectacle Lake has one unpopulated basin located on the Reservation where the sample is taken.  The other basin is not sampled and has a few houses.  The rest of the lakeshore is owned by the forest service.

Name: South Pond
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: South Pond is a stained pond bordered by a swamp on the west side and a road on the east.  South Pond is the most populated inland pond/lake on the reservation.

Name: Sugar Island
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: St. Mary's River is sampled above Sugar Island Lands in the middle of the shipping channel.   This site is located downstream from a bi-national Area of Concern.

Name: Wetland 1
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Wetland 1 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled in a slow flowing spring near an old dump site.

Name: Wetland 2
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Wetland 2 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled in a intermittently wet area that is used by recreational ORVs.

Name: Wetland 3
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Wetland 3 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled due to its convenient location and water level.  The water level in wetland 3 is the highest of the 3 wetland sites.

Name: Wharf 1
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Boat docking area in need of shoreline restoration.

Name: Wharf 2
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Boat docking area in need of shoreline restoration.

Name: Waishkey River
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: The Waishkey River is a 5th order stream that is the largest inlet to Back Bay.  The river and its tributaries run through mostly argricultural and forested land.

Name: Waishkey River 1A
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Waishkey River sampled just downstream of the confluence of Besseau Creek.  WR1a is also sampled directly downstream of the M28 road-crossing.

Name: Waishkey River 1B
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Waishkey River sampled just upstream of a tributary that may drain a private sewage lagoon.  Sampled just downstream of WR1a.

Name: Waishkey River 1C
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Waishkey River sampled directly downstream of WR1b and a tributary that may drain a private sewage lagoon.

Name: Waishkey River 2A
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Waishkey River Sampled directly upstream of confluence with Orrus Creek.

Name: Waishkey River 2B
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Waishkey River Sampled directly downstream of confluence with Orrus Creek.

Name: Waishkey River 3
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: East Branch of the Waishkey River sampled directly upstream to the confluence with the West Branch of the Waishkey River.

Name: Waishkey River 4
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: West Branch of the Waishkey River sampled directly upstream to the confluence with the East Branch of the Waishkey River.

Name: Waishkey River 5
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: South Branch of the East Branch of the WR, sampled at S. Touri Rd., downstream of the town of Dafter, Michigan.

Name: Waishkey River 6
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Headwaters of the South Branch of the East Branch of the WR, sampled at 11 Mile Rd.

Name: Waishkey River 7
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: South Branch of the East Branch of the WR, sampled just upstream of the confluence to E Branch.

Name: Waishkey River 8
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: Confluence of Besseau Creek and South Branch of Besseau Creek; Sampled at S. Bound Rd.

Name: Waishkey River 9
Monitoring_Location_Description_Text: South Branch of the WR, sampled at confluence of two major tributaries at Tilton Rd.
